caption: I love their classic Banh Mi! They are also are extremely fast and kind. They once gave me a free bottle of water cause I was clearly out of breath, sweating, and in a rush during a busy work day trying to run and grab a sandwich from them. Truly excellent quality and service. My top Banh Mi place in BK!

best banh mi in new york. the food is always consistent, the delivery is always lightning fast, and everyone who works there is so friendly. this is the restaurant i miss the most any time i'm away from home. would give them 8 stars if i could

I only ordered delivery, and I was happy with it. The food arrived well packaged, and the pho broth was separate from the solids, which is a sign that the restaurant knows its stuff. I loved the summer rolls because they were tasty, fresh, and thick. The sardine sandwich had a good amount of ingredients, and the bread was the perfect blend of soft inside and crunchy crust. I wasn't too excited with the beef pho, which was rather bland compared to the other two options.
Unfortunately the quality of the pork sandwich went from good to very bad, I couldn’t even finish it, it didn’t taste like pork at all and the Thai ice tea was water down😔
(Translated by Google) Best bahn mi around!  (Original) Best bahn mi around!
Yummy and well priced!
We have been coming here for years! They have such good bubble tea, and amazing service.
I ate here all the time before the pandemic hit. But since they reopened I ate there twice and got really bad stomach aches.😟

Delicious food, always fresh! The banh mi sandwiches and pho are divine, and the bubble tea is always thirst-quenching! Prices are very reasonable, the staff are delightful, and I always get excellent service. I highly recommend it!

I really like this place - but not just only for the food.  The food is good, I always get the grilled pork banh mi and the mango juice after the climbing gym every weekend.  It's cheap, filling, and quick.  Now for the added point - I've ordered delivery from here a few times and tried ordering a grilled pork chop rice dish instead today.  The pork was unfortunately extremely burnt when it came.  I called seamless and they called Lotus, and eventually told me to call Lotus directly.  However, they called me immediately before I could and offered to send a brand new one at no cost.  Very nice and shows they care.  I will be a loyal customer!
The owners are really nice and their sandwiches are delicious.
I had the vegetarian pho with the tofu chicken. The noodles and broth were delicious. The fake meat was different from what I expected and wittle strange. Overall very delicious and affordable.
Their sandwiches are so good. Don't miss this gem.
Good pho
I ordered takeout and the food got to me in a timely manner and was also very good. Vegetarian chicken pho and 2 sandwiches. made me a happy camper

I suggest eating in their restaurant. I ordered delivery. This was supposed to be Tofu Vegatable Pho and all I got was Tofu and noodles, there was no broccoli, mushrooms, bok choy.... Not worth the $$  Spring rolls are delicious though. 👍🏼
I haven't try the food but the bubble tea is good
Great Vietnamese sandwiches.  (Duh).
I love that the food is always fresh and delicious! +E Recording Artist-Edwin Vazquez

Service was great! Very attentive staff! Chopped salad is amazing Alon with the Spaghetti and balls!! Special shout out to Calvin for taking the time to email my receipt!! Will definitely be going again next time I'm in the area!! Lotus Vietnamese Sandwiches
Solid sandwiches and cheap prices 👌
Excellent inexpensive place for Vietnamese sandwiches
Food is OK, except for that piece of glass! I'm lucky it was on top!
the grilled pork chop over rice is too dry and hard, but i love their Vietnamese sandwich.
Long-standing, affordable place with excellent service. I only wish I were still able to eat gluten, their bread is AMAZING.
Good food
Service was great with good food. Recommend everyone to try something here!
Just a nice cheapo place for a bubble tea and a good Vietnamese sandwich. 10 bucks at lunch. Sandwich is fresh and tasty. Bubble tea is good too. What’s not to like?
Best bahn mi around. Great bubble tea too. This is a regular Saturday lunch stop for us as we run errands in the neighborhood. The usual guy working there always has a smile for us.
the summer rolls are irresistible.....yummy!!!
Classic sandwich is consistently fantastic.
Really great place to grab a quick Bahn Mi!
Best Vietnamese sandwiches on 5th! Love the sandwich and bubble tea lunch special.
We were out on the hunt for a great sandwich and this place did not disappointed! Will definitely be back.

I’ve been eating here for four years now. The service is always great and the food is always fresh! The shredded chicken pho is my usual order but I decided to try my first Bhan sandwich. Fooken amazing!!! This is worth my money.
I order from here a few times a week. Great lunch specials.
Pretty yummy and really good prices!

These people are so nice! I accidentally ordered the wrong thing, so they offered to simply deliver to me what I had meant to order. They didn’t even charge me! And of course, all the food is absolutely delicious. Great customer service and very fast!
Solid banhmi sandwiches, super fast delivery.
Love their Vietnamese chicken sandwich
Absolute best Vietnamese classic sandwich!
Good sandwich fast service
Love those sandwiches
Good and cheaper places to small bites and good sandwiches.
Excellent sandwiches!!!

If I can give no stars. I would. I asked for a non spicy sandwich. No big deal. I Seen the woman Making my order add something I asked not to. Now, the other woman who took the order noticed and stood in front of my view assuming I didn't see anything becausebi was gazing. Now I turn to her instantly and have this look of disgust, she saw my expression and she pretended to have just noticed and starts telling me she will make a fresh one. She just passed her a napkin to wipe it off. But she literally acts like I am an idiot.  Then the woman got defensive and starts carrying on and what looks to be the manager has to literally grab her and drag her to the back. And now I hear her yelling from the back. I'm blown away. As many times as I have came there never expected such terrible service and customer service. Not coming back. Completely  Disgusted.
Best grill pork sandwich HANDS down!! Not expensive at all.. Good quality
I love their sandwiches, and the sriracha bottles on the side rule.
Wonderful. Great price and very impressed by how good the classic sandwich was. Will definitely return.
Price on internet is not the same as inside. I did ask them to made it not crispy(my lips are sensitive)they didn't made it so. So hats why "Naaahh..."
Best Bahn Mi I've ever eaten!
Came in to get hot pho but there was no heat on inside. Must have been below 50 degrees inside. Beef pho was not very good, worst I ever had.
Simple, delicious.
Quality banh mi and bubble teas at reasonable prices.
Classic Bon Mi is the bomb!
Friendly staff, great space,  delicious food. First time here, but it won't be the last!

Small counter service spot. My first introduction to a Vietnamese sandwich and I've been back many times since. I go for the classic spicy and sometimes a coconut bubble tea.  I wish they would chop the cilantro though. They put the whole plant, stems and all, in the sandwich. They have no problem holding the cilantro if you ask.
Great Bahn Sandwiches, great Bubble Tea. I've driven out of my way plenty if times to hit up this spot. Trust me, the sandwiches rock and the the staff is very nice too.
Amazing. I love the grilled pork with white rice..Ordering it right now :)
Sandwiches are great, the bread seems to be plain NY deli hero bread, but still good.
The sandwichs from this place have attained legendary status among my friends and I.

There are a few other Banh Mi places within a few blocks, but this one is my favorite. Quick snadwich assemblage, the bread is just crusty enough and the vegetables are julienned perfectly. There are a few tables for sitting and a laundry list of bubble tea options to choose from.

Yum! I get banh mi ("classic sandwich" on the menu) a couple times a month from this place. Fresh crusty french bread and crisp pickled veg means the sandwich is always delicious. Definitely recommend!
Viet sandwiches delicious
